HEADWORD: Cronartium
<hw>Cronartium</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A genus of rust fungi having
aecia produced in raised or swollen sori and teliospores borne in waxy
columns.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Cronartium</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
